
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `memusage` baraye didan meghdare estefade shode az hafize (RAM) be vasileye har process dar system estefade mishavad. In dastoor komak mikonad ta process-haee ke hafize ziadi estefade mikonand ra peyda konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `memusage -p <PID>` --> 🎯 Namayesh estefade az hafize baraye yek process khas ba PID moshakhas.
    🔹 `memusage -u <username>` --> 👤 Namayesh estefade az hafize baraye hameye process-ha ke az tarighe yek karbar khass ejra mishavand.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ memusage
    
    🔹 Namayesh listi az process-ha va meghdare hafize ke har yek estefade mikonand.

    $ memusage -p 1234
    
    🔹 Namayesh etela'at tafsili darbareye process ba PID 1234.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ memusage | grep firefox
    
    🔹 Estefade az `grep` baraye peyda kardane process `firefox` va namayesh meghdare hafeze estefade shode.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `memusage` command is used to display the memory usage of processes running on the system. It helps identify processes that consume a significant amount of memory.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `memusage -p <PID>` --> 🎯 Display memory usage for a specific process with the given PID.
    🔹 `memusage -u <username>` --> 👤 Display memory usage for all processes owned by a particular user.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ memusage
    
    🔹 Displays a list of processes and their respective memory usage.

    $ memusage -p 1234
    
    🔹 Displays detailed information about the process with PID 1234.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ memusage | grep firefox
    
    🔹 Uses `grep` to find the `firefox` process and display its memory usage.
